# profiling vim plugins
# https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12213597/how-to-see-which-plugins-are-making-vim-slow
:profile start profile.log
:profile func *
:profile file *
" do some actions..
:profile pause
:noautocmd qall!

# leap.nvim
s                 forward search
S                 backward search
s{char}<space>    target char at end of line
s<space><space>   jump to an empty line
s<enter>          repeat the last search
s<enter><enter>   traverse matches
x                 move lhs visual bound
X                 move rhs visual bound

# vim-emoji
;e    replace all `:emoji:` instances in current buffer

# fzf
;a  # ag
;j  # notes

# LeaderF
<c-f> search files
<c-p> search mru

<c-r> toggle fuzzy/regex mode
<c-f> toggle fullpath
<c-u> clear prompt
<c-j> down
<c-k> up
<c-p> preview
<tab> normal mode

<up>/<down> navigate history

# indent guides
:IndentGuidesToggle

# vCoolor
<alt-c>  open color picker
